WorldStage Newsonline– LASACO Assurance Plc, a major player in the Nigerian insurance sector has issued a notice of its earnings forecast for the second quarter ending 30 June 2021 with a projection of N3.171 billion gross premium written, down from N5.40 billion projected for first quarter (Q1) 2021. The forecast released at the Nigerian Stock Exchange also showed N205.129 million profit for the period, a 45.33% cut back from N375.229 million projected for Q1 2021. WorldStage earlier reported LASACO’s earnings forecast for the first quarter ending 31 March 2021 with a projection of N5.40 billion gross premium written, up from N1.323 billion in fourth quarter (Q4) 2020